  "body": "- [ ] I didn't [opened a support ticket](https://trufflesuite.zendesk.com/hc/en-us/requests/new) before filing this issue, because is a technical issue.\r\n\r\n---------------------------\r\n\r\n## Issue\r\n\r\nThe way the require package works is making impossible to me to get truffle migrations working with typescript without having to compile. if you go to the require package at `require.js` the way Require.file method(lines 19 to 99) work, makes it imposible to use ts-node to run typescript in place, if it was just a regular require it would be so easy to use typescript, i would be glad to improve this i just wanted to know why is it done like that, why do you need to do al that stuff in order to require the package?\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nIf i use ts-node to run truffle migrate, i should be able to run typescript migrations\r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n\r\nAs typescript files are not actually being required as regular modules, ts-node/register cannot work properly therefore syntax errors comes up\r\n<img width=\"646\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2022-01-04 at 19 02 48\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/65319051/148129919-3ca82424-4139-4a55-bc69-193d1087f7fb.png\">\r\n\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System: MacOS\r\n* Ethereum client: Ganache\r\n* Truffle version (`5.4.26`):\r\n* node version (`16.10.0`):\r\n* yarn version (`1.22.17`): \r\n",
